result.execSummary:
The defendant Lachanda D. Neal was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Retail Theft - Intentionally Take (<=$500) [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Attorney Debra Van Wormer O'Rourke in court for Defendant Lachanda D. Neal. Prosecuting Atty Dennis Joseph Ryan appeared for State of Wisconsin. Defendant Lachanda D. Neal appeared by video means.  State moves amend to 943.50(1)(m).  Attorney ORourke gives agreement reached.  State agrees.  Defendant agrees and understands.  No contest Plea entered, advised of constitutional rights, plea accepted by Court.  Court finds Defendant guilty.  Court imposes sentence.
Count 1 as amended:
$243.00 costs, $200.00 DNA and $10.00 surcharge, 60 days to pay or set up a payment plan.
10 Days in Sauk County Jail, with huber, consecutive.  Transfer to Dane County Jail approved, per jail rules.  2 days jail credit.
Restitution paid in full in court.
